<attribute>
  <id>ATTR_CONTAINED_EQ_PGOODS</id>
  <targetType>TARGET_TYPE_PROC_CHIP</targetType>
  <description>
    During a contained IPL the EQ partial-good configuration needs to be saved
    and restored since the actual registers are clobbered when re-executing the
    subset of istep3 procedures.
    Array structure: ATTR_CONTAINED_EQ_PGOODS[quad][reg], where there are 8
    possible quads and one register per-quad.
  </description>
  <valueType>uint64</valueType>
  <array>8</array>
  <default>
    0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0
  </default>
  <writeable/>
</attribute>
<attribute>
  <id>ATTR_CONTAINED_FENCE_HANGPULSE</id>
  <targetType>TARGET_TYPE_PROC_CHIP</targetType>
  <description>
    By default, the contained IPL fences off hang pulses because they are
    asynchronous to the core and will compromise cycle reproducibility if not
    fenced.
    Some DFT applications require hang pulse to be enabled during contained
    IPL (DTS sampling during TDP workloads in mfg).
  </description>
  <valueType>uint8</valueType>
  <enum>
    OFF = 0x0,
    ON = 0x1
  </enum>
  <default>ON</default>
  <writeable/>
